Details: each matrix may use different measurement scales. To
properly use MCIA each matrix must undergo variable-level
normalization (e.g. mean-centered) as well as block level (e.g. YY)
Details: MCIA uses an optimization protocol to account for shared
and omic-specific factors to reduce the p features into r factors. For
illustrative purposes we are using r=3.
Details: Block-based matrices are intermediate
matrices which are used during the optimization
process. Shown here for completeness of
documentation and general understanding.
Details: Global-based matrices can be used for several
downstream analyses.
Details: Optimization attempts to create a lower
dimensional repesentation that maximizes the
covariance betwen the block scores and global
scores.
